				\begin{document}$$Moisture \; removed=m_{p}\frac{M_{i}-M_{f}}{100-M_{f})}$$\end{document}
where, mp—Initial mass of biomass (g), Mi and Mf are initial moisture content and final moisture content respectively (in %).
The total energy required to evaporate the water content from the sampleE=mpCΔT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
